194	[K\"ahler module of a localization is trivial]
195	  \label{lem:kaehler_localization_subsingleton}
196	  \lean{AlgebraicGeometry.Scheme.kaehler_localization_subsingleton}
197	  Let $A \to L$ be a localization at a multiplicative subset $M \subseteq A$. Then $\Omega_{L / A}$ is subsingleton (the zero $L$-module).
