\section{Bridge: presheaf form $\leftrightarrow$ algebra-K\"ahler form on an affine chart (milestone M1)}
\label{sec:bridge}

Theorem~\ref{thm:smooth_locally_free_omega} is stated in the \emph{algebra-K\"ahler form} $\Omega_{\Gamma(X, V) / \Gamma(S, U)}$ for an affine chart $V \subseteq f^{-1}U$, while the relative cotangent presheaf $\Omega_{X/S}$ of Definition~\ref{def:relative_kaehler_presheaf} carries on its section over $V$ the K\"ahler module $\Omega_{\Gamma(X, V) / A_{\mathrm{colim}}}$ over the presheaf-level inverse-image colimit ring $A_{\mathrm{colim}} = (f^{-1}_{\mathrm{psh}}\struct{S})(V) = \mathrm{colim}_{W :\, f V \subseteq W \subseteq S}\,\struct{S}(W)$. On a single affine chart the two are connected by a canonical $B$-linear isomorphism whose construction is the content of milestone~M1 of the project roadmap (\texttt{STRATEGY.md}).

\begin{theorem}\leanok
[Bridge between presheaf and algebra-K\"ahler forms]
  \label{thm:relativeDifferentialsPresheaf_equiv_kaehler_appLE}
  \lean{AlgebraicGeometry.Scheme.relativeDifferentialsPresheaf_equiv_kaehler_appLE}
  \uses{def:relative_kaehler_presheaf, lem:relative_kaehler_presheaf_obj, lem:appLE_isLocalization}
  Let $f \colon X \to S$ be a morphism of schemes, let $U \subseteq S$ and $V \subseteq X$ be affine opens with $V \leq f^{-1}U$, and write $A := \Gamma(S, U)$, $B := \Gamma(X, V)$, with the appLE algebra structure $A \to B$ induced by $f$. There is a canonical $B$-linear equivalence
  \[
    (\mathrm{relativeDifferentialsPresheaf}\,f).\mathrm{presheaf}(V)
    \;\simeq_{B}\;
    \Omega_{B \,/\, A}
  \]
  identifying the section module of the relative cotangent presheaf on $V$ with the appLE-algebra K\"ahler differential module of Theorem~\ref{thm:smooth_locally_free_omega}. The Lean target packages this as a \texttt{LinearEquiv} (\texttt{≃ₗ[B]}), mirroring Mathlib's convention for \texttt{KaehlerDifferential.tensorKaehlerEquivOfFormallyEtale}.
\end{theorem}

\begin{proof}
  \uses{def:relative_kaehler_presheaf, lem:relative_kaehler_presheaf_obj, lem:appLE_isLocalization, lem:kaehler_localization_subsingleton, lem:kaehler_quotient_localization_iso}
  \leanok
  The proof decomposes into the four sub-steps M1.a--M1.e of the roadmap. We use the abbreviation $A_{\mathrm{colim}} := (f^{-1}_{\mathrm{psh}}\struct{S})(V) = \mathrm{colim}_{W :\, f V \subseteq W \subseteq S}\,\struct{S}(W)$ for the colimit ring carrying the presheaf-side K\"ahler module.

  \emph{M1.a: the multiplicative set of ``good'' elements.} Define
  \[
    M \;:=\; \{\, g \in A \,:\, (f.\mathrm{appLE}\,U\,V\,e).\mathrm{hom}(g) \in B^{\times} \,\}
  \]
  as the set of elements of $A$ whose image in $B$ is a unit (formalized as \lean{AlgebraicGeometry.IsAffineOpen.appLE_unitSubmonoid}). $M$ is a submonoid: $1 \in M$ (the appLE map is a ring homomorphism, so $\mathrm{appLE}(1) = 1$, a unit), and if $g, h \in M$ then $\mathrm{appLE}(gh) = \mathrm{appLE}(g)\,\mathrm{appLE}(h) \in B^{\times}$ as the product of two units.

  \emph{M1.b: $A \to A_{\mathrm{colim}}$ is the localization at $M$.} This is the heart of the bridge and is recorded as Lemma~\ref{lem:appLE_isLocalization} below. The argument re-frames the colimit comparison as a direct \texttt{IsLocalization} check via the two-direction \emph{equivalence-based} pattern: build the two ring homomorphisms $A_M \to A_{\mathrm{colim}}$ (via the universal property of \texttt{Localization}~$M$, after observing that each $g \in M$ is already a unit in $A_{\mathrm{colim}}$) and $A_{\mathrm{colim}} \to A_M$ (via the cocone universal property, using basic-open refinements $D(g) \subseteq W$ for each open $W \supseteq f V$ to factor through some $A_g$), then verify the composites are identities via \texttt{IsLocalization.ringHom\_ext}, package them as an algebra-equivalence $A_M \simeq_A A_{\mathrm{colim}}$, and conclude \texttt{IsLocalization}~$M$~$A_{\mathrm{colim}}$ via \texttt{IsLocalization.isLocalization\_of\_algEquiv}~\texttt{[verified iter-123 analogist]}. This pattern avoids the \texttt{Functor.Final} colim-comparison framing entirely (Mathlib has no off-the-shelf ``colim of localizations is localization at the union submonoid'' lemma; the analogist-verified pattern is the two-direction equivalence-based construction; \texttt{IsLocalization.of\_le} is a structurally different pattern relating localizations at $M \subseteq N$). The single-element-localization fact $\struct{S}(D(g)) = A_g$ is supplied by Mathlib's \texttt{AlgebraicGeometry.IsAffineOpen.isLocalization\_basicOpen}.

  \emph{M1.c: the K\"ahler module of a localization is trivial.} Mathlib already supplies this: by \texttt{Algebra.FormallyUnramified.of\_isLocalization} (\texttt{Mathlib.RingTheory.Unramified.Basic}), the algebra map $A \to A_{\mathrm{colim}}$ is \texttt{FormallyUnramified}; and the instance \texttt{Algebra.FormallyUnramified.subsingleton\_kaehlerDifferential} (same file) then gives $\Subsingleton\,\Omega_{A_{\mathrm{colim}} / A}$. The project-side Lemma~\ref{lem:kaehler_localization_subsingleton} re-exports this conclusion in two lines (no genuine Mathlib gap-fill is needed here, contra an earlier framing of M1.c).

  \emph{M1.d: the surjection $\Omega_{B/A} \twoheadrightarrow \Omega_{B/A_{\mathrm{colim}}}$ is an iso.} Apply Lemma~\ref{lem:kaehler_quotient_localization_iso} below (\texttt{KaehlerDifferential.isLocalizedModule\_map} in Mathlib \texttt{RingTheory.Etale.Kaehler}, plus the M1.c conclusion that $\Omega_{A_{\mathrm{colim}}/A} = 0$). The second fundamental exact sequence
  \[
    B \otimes_{A_{\mathrm{colim}}} \Omega_{A_{\mathrm{colim}} / A}
    \;\longrightarrow\; \Omega_{B / A}
    \;\twoheadrightarrow\; \Omega_{B / A_{\mathrm{colim}}}
    \;\longrightarrow\; 0
  \]
  has zero left-hand term by M1.c, so the right-hand surjection is an iso.

  \emph{M1.e: combine with the $\mathrm{rfl}$-identification of the presheaf section.} By Lemma~\ref{lem:relative_kaehler_presheaf_obj}, $(\mathrm{relativeDifferentialsPresheaf}\,f).\mathrm{presheaf}(V) = \Omega_{B / A_{\mathrm{colim}}}$ definitionally. Composing the rfl-equality with the inverse of the M1.d iso gives the claimed $B$-linear isomorphism. The cocone-leg factorisation identity $(A \to A_{\mathrm{colim}} \to B) = f.\mathrm{appLE}\,U\,V\,e$ that establishes the \texttt{IsScalarTower}~$A$~$A_{\mathrm{colim}}$~$B$ instance feeding M1.d is named \lean{AlgebraicGeometry.IsAffineOpen.appLE_colimRingHom_comp_φV} in the Lean source.
\end{proof}

\begin{lemma}\leanok
[$A \to A_{\mathrm{colim}}$ is a localization at $M$]
  \label{lem:appLE_isLocalization}
  \lean{AlgebraicGeometry.IsAffineOpen.appLE_isLocalization}
  \uses{def:relative_kaehler_presheaf}
  In the setting of Theorem~\ref{thm:relativeDifferentialsPresheaf_equiv_kaehler_appLE}, the canonical ring homomorphism $A \to A_{\mathrm{colim}}$ exhibits $A_{\mathrm{colim}}$ as the localization of $A$ at the multiplicative set $M := \{g \in A : (f.\mathrm{appLE}\,U\,V\,e).\mathrm{hom}(g) \in B^{\times}\}$.
\end{lemma}

\begin{proof}
  \uses{def:relative_kaehler_presheaf}
  \leanok
  We construct the \texttt{IsLocalization}~$M$~$A_{\mathrm{colim}}$ predicate directly via the two-direction \emph{equivalence-based} pattern: build forward + backward ring maps, verify the two inverse identities, package them as an algebra-equivalence $A_M \simeq_{A} A_{\mathrm{colim}}$, and conclude \texttt{IsLocalization}~$M$~$A_{\mathrm{colim}}$ via \texttt{IsLocalization.isLocalization\_of\_algEquiv}~\texttt{[verified]} (the iter-123 mathlib-analogist consult verified that this lemma takes an \texttt{AlgEquiv}, not a \texttt{RingEquiv}, and that \texttt{IsLocalization.of\_le} is a structurally different pattern relating localizations at $M \subseteq N$, not equivalence-based). The pattern avoids any \texttt{Functor.Final} colim-comparison (Mathlib snapshot \texttt{b80f227} has no off-the-shelf ``colim of localizations is localization at the union submonoid'' lemma, so this pattern is the canonical project-local route).

  \emph{Step 0: each $g \in M$ is a unit in $A_{\mathrm{colim}}$ (formalized as the top-level helper \lean{AlgebraicGeometry.IsAffineOpen.isUnit_appLE_unitSubmonoid_in_colim}, closed iter-122).} Fix $g \in M$, so $\mathrm{appLE}(g) \in B^{\times}$. The basic open $D(g) \subseteq U$ contains $f V$ (by the bridge identity $f V \subseteq D(g) \iff \mathrm{appLE}(g) \in B^{\times}$, following from \texttt{Mathlib.AlgebraicGeometry.AffineScheme}'s \texttt{IsAffineOpen.basicOpen\_eq\_iff\_isUnit} together with $D(g) = f^{-1}\,U.\mathrm{basicOpen}\,g$ on the affine source side). The cocone leg of the directed colimit corresponding to the open $D(g)$ produces a ring map $\struct{S}(D(g)) \to A_{\mathrm{colim}}$, and on $D(g)$ itself the element $g$ is invertible (\texttt{AlgebraicGeometry.IsAffineOpen.isLocalization\_basicOpen} supplies the \texttt{IsLocalization.Away}~$g$~$\struct{S}(D(g))$ instance, so $g$ is a unit in $\struct{S}(D(g))$). Pushing this unit through the cocone leg shows $g$ is a unit in $A_{\mathrm{colim}}$.

  \emph{Step 1: the algebra map $A_M \to A_{\mathrm{colim}}$.} The universal property of \texttt{Localization}~$M$ (\texttt{IsLocalization.lift}, \texttt{Mathlib.RingTheory.Localization.Basic}) applied to the algebra map $A \to A_{\mathrm{colim}}$ — together with Step 0 — produces a ring homomorphism $\varphi \colon A_M \to A_{\mathrm{colim}}$ over $A$.

  \emph{Step 2: the algebra map $A_{\mathrm{colim}} \to A_M$.} The colimit $A_{\mathrm{colim}}$ has the universal property of the cocone over $\{\struct{S}(W) : f V \subseteq W \subseteq S\}$; to produce a ring map out of $A_{\mathrm{colim}}$ it suffices to specify a compatible family of ring maps from each cocone node. For each open $W \supseteq f V$, restrict to $W \subseteq U$ (intersecting with $U$ preserves the cocone since $f V \subseteq U$), cover $W \cap U$ by basic opens $D(g_i) \subseteq U$ (\texttt{PrimeSpectrum.isBasis\_basic\_opens}), use quasi-compactness of $f V$ to extract a finite sub-cover, take $g := \prod g_i$ so that $D(g) \subseteq W \cap U$ and $f V \subseteq D(g)$ (i.e.\ $g \in M$); then $\struct{S}(W) \to \struct{S}(D(g)) = A_g \to A_M$ via the canonical $A_g \to A_M$ supplied by the inclusion of submonoids $\langle g \rangle \subseteq M$. Compatibility on intersections follows from the universal property of $A_g$ at each level.

  \emph{Step 3: composites are identities.} \texttt{IsLocalization.ringHom\_ext} (\texttt{Mathlib.RingTheory.Localization.Basic}) shows that any two ring homomorphisms $A_M \to R$ agreeing on the image of $A$ are equal. The composite $A_M \to A_{\mathrm{colim}} \to A_M$ agrees with the identity on $A$ (both send $a \mapsto a/1$), hence is the identity. Symmetrically, any two ring homomorphisms $A_{\mathrm{colim}} \to R$ agreeing on every cocone node $\struct{S}(W)$ are equal; the composite $A_{\mathrm{colim}} \to A_M \to A_{\mathrm{colim}}$ agrees with the identity on every $\struct{S}(D(g))$ for $g \in M$ (both factor through the canonical $\struct{S}(D(g)) \to A_{\mathrm{colim}}$), and basic opens with $g \in M$ form a cofinal subfamily of opens containing $f V$, so the composite is the identity on the whole colimit.

  \emph{Step 4: conclude \texttt{IsLocalization}~$M$~$A_{\mathrm{colim}}$.} The algebra-equivalence $A_M \simeq_{A} A_{\mathrm{colim}}$ assembled from the forward (Step 1) and backward (Step 2) maps together with the inverse identities (Step 3) — combined with the canonical \texttt{IsLocalization}~$M$~$(\texttt{Localization}~M)$ instance — yields \texttt{IsLocalization}~$M$~$A_{\mathrm{colim}}$ via \texttt{IsLocalization.isLocalization\_of\_algEquiv}~\texttt{[verified]} (\texttt{Mathlib.RingTheory.Localization.Basic}). The iter-123 mathlib-analogist consult verified that this constructor takes an \texttt{AlgEquiv} (not a bare \texttt{RingEquiv}); the algebra structures on the two sides are \texttt{Localization.instAlgebra} on $A_M$ and the project-local \texttt{appLE\_colimAlgebra} on $A_{\mathrm{colim}}$ (transported from the cocone leg's ring-hom).

  \emph{Mathlib leverage summary.} The five \texttt{[verified]} closure pieces are
  \texttt{AlgebraicGeometry.IsAffineOpen.isLocalization\_basicOpen} (Steps 0, 2),
  \texttt{AlgebraicGeometry.IsAffineOpen.basicOpen\_eq\_iff\_isUnit} (Step 0 bridge identity),
  \texttt{IsLocalization.lift} (Step 1),
  \texttt{IsLocalization.ringHom\_ext} (Step 3), and
  \texttt{IsLocalization.isLocalization\_of\_algEquiv} (Step 4).
  The cocone leg-morphisms of \texttt{TopCat.Presheaf.pullback} are verified to exist in Mathlib snapshot \texttt{b80f227}.

  The Mathlib analogist's persistent file \texttt{analogies/relative-differentials-presheaf-bridge.md} (iter-121) records the full design rationale for the chosen API shape.
\end{proof}

\begin{remark}[M1 parked iter-125; bijectivity recipe for unparking]
  \label{rem:m1_parked_iter125}
  As of iter-125 the lemma is closed up to a single residual sorry inside the in-body construction of the algebra-equivalence $A_M \simeq_A A_{\mathrm{colim}}$. Concretely: the iter-124 prover packaged Step 1 + Step 4 via \texttt{IsLocalization.lift} + \texttt{IsLocalization.isLocalization\_of\_algEquiv}, promoted the forward map to an \texttt{AlgHom} \texttt{forwardAlg} (closing the \texttt{commutes'} field in body via \texttt{RingHom.congr\_fun}), and reduced Steps 2 + 3 to the single claim \texttt{Function.Bijective}~$\lceil\!\mathtt{forwardAlg}\!\rceil$ via \texttt{AlgEquiv.ofBijective}. The residual at \texttt{Differentials.lean:398} is therefore the bijectivity of \texttt{forwardAlg}, which by Mathlib's \texttt{IsLocalization.lift\_injective\_iff} + \texttt{IsLocalization.lift\_surjective\_iff} decomposes into two questions: (a) ``for $x, y \in A$, does $\mathrm{appLE\_colimRingHom}(x) = \mathrm{appLE\_colimRingHom}(y)$ in $A_{\mathrm{colim}}$ force the existence of $g \in M$ with $g(x - y) = 0$ in $A$?''~(injectivity), and (b) ``is every $v \in A_{\mathrm{colim}}$ of the form $\mathrm{appLE\_colimRingHom}(a) / \mathrm{appLE\_colimRingHom}(s)$ for some $a \in A, s \in M$?''~(surjectivity). Both questions reduce to the same two Mathlib pieces: \emph{filtered-colim element representation} for the lan-defined colim of \texttt{CommRingCat} (the bridge \texttt{IsPointwiseLeftKanExtensionAt} $\Rightarrow$ \texttt{CommRingCat.FilteredColimits.colimitCocone} explicit elements; ~50--80 LOC of category bookkeeping) and \emph{basic-open cofinality} for the submonoid $M$ inside the opens lattice (use quasi-compactness of $f V$ + \texttt{IsAffineOpen.exists\_basicOpen\_le} pointwise + a finite-cover assembly to a single $g \in M$; ~50--80 LOC). The route survives unchanged from the M1.b proof above; only the \emph{packaging} of the conclusion differs (Step 4 via algebra-equivalence vs.\ Step 4 via bijectivity of the forward AlgHom). The full recipe is recorded at \texttt{.archon/logs/iter-124/task\_results-archive/AlgebraicJacobian\_Differentials.lean.md} for whoever unparks M1.
\end{remark}

